V N K  -  L I N U X  L I N K E D  L I S T  E X A M P L E  M O D U L E

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A U T H O R:

Loi Huynh

DESCRIPTION:

This is an example about Linux C Linked List.
There are three main types of linked list:
- Singly Linked List
- Doubly Linked List
- Circular Linked List
In this example, I present the first type of linked list - Singly Linked List.
|------|------|           |------|------|
| DATA | NEXT |---------->| DATA | NEXT |--------> XXXX
|------|------|           |------|------|

BINARY NAME:

[vnklili]

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

USING:

#>:$ cd VNK_LinkedListExample/build
#>:$ VNK_MBuild.bash -g         # To generate Makefile via CMAKE
#>:$ VNK_MBuild.bash -m         # To call "make"
#>:$ VNK_MBuild.bash -h         # To show build help
#>:$ ./vnklili <arguments>      # To run built binary

TIPS:

- Call "VNK_MBuild.bash -g -m" to generate Makefile and doing "make" in a time.
  Or you can simply call "VNK_MBuild.bash -gm".

NOTICE:

- You can need to build libs firstly.
- Example: to build libVNK_LibNotify_static.a, navigate to
  VNK_Library/VNK_LibNotify/build and call "VNK_MBuild.bash -g -m".

OTHERS:

- Build script name: VNK_MBuild.bash.

REFERENCES:

- https://www.learn-c.org/en/Linked_lists
- https://www.programiz.com/dsa/linked-list-types
- https://www.tutorialspoint.com/data_structures_algorithms/linked_list_\
  algorithms.htm

